[SN]TITLE[SN]
Thief steals 200m of phone cable in St Fagans, Cardiff

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Some homes and businesses in Cardiff are without phone lines or broadband after a thief stole 200m of cable.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The theft happened at about 08:00 GMT on Saturday near St Fagans Road, St Fagans, and South Wales Police said it has "affected a whole community".
Photos of a man they want to speak to in connection with the theft have been released.
Service providers are working to restore the service to the affected properties.
